      "Incident documented and reported to BSEE"
    ],
    "summary": "During a well workover operation on November 8, 2016, a wireline parted while the Crane Operator was hoisting the lubricator and tool string from the wellhead tree. The tool string dropped approximately 10 feet to the deck, resulting in minor damage to the tool string end (bent tip). No injuries were reported. The root cause was the Assistant Wireline Operator's failure to provide adequate slack in the wireline prior to hoisting.",
